figured by chat.",iconClassName:"text-blue-500"},{icon:x2,title:"Lovable Cloud database",description:"Enable Lovable Cloud, run live SQL, and pull connection info, all from your agent. Reads, writes, and schema changes.",iconClassName:"text-emerald-500"},{icon:X2,title:"Deploy to production",description:"Trigger a deploy from your agent and get back a live URL. Iterate and share, all programmatically.",iconClassName:"text-rose-500"},{icon:T2,title:"Workspaces & projects",description:"List projects, fetch metadata, manage workspaces. Everything an agent needs to operate across all your Lovable projects.",iconClassName:"text-cyan-500"},{icon:m2,title:"Persistent knowledge",description:"Set workspace and project knowledge so Lovable follows your standards, brand, and API patterns on every run.",iconClassName:"text-amber-500"},{icon:u2,title:"Built for agents",description:"Typed tool schemas, structured outputs, and clear error responses. Designed for agents from day one.",iconClassName:"text-violet-500"}],Qd=[{question:"What is MCP?",answer:"The Model Context Protocol is an open standard that lets AI agents discover and call external tools. When an agent connects to an MCP server, it can see what tools are available and decide when to use them. Lovable's MCP server makes Lovable one of those tools, findable, invokable, and composable."},{question:"Which clients can I use?",answer:"OAuth is currently supported for the assistant and editor clients listed in the setup section below. Other MCP clients cannot complete the OAuth flow at this time."},{question:"What's the difference between this and Lovable's chat connectors?",answer:"Chat connectors let the Lovable agent connect to your external tools (Notion, Linear, Miro, and so on) during a build. The Lovable MCP server is the reverse: it lets your assistant or editor connect to Lovable and drive it programmatically."},{question:"Is it included in my plan?",answer:"Yes — the Lovable MCP server is available on every plan, including Free. Enterprise customers should reach out to their account executive to enable it for their workspace."},{question:"Can I connect with an API key?",answer:"Not currently. OAuth is the only supported way to connect. The MCP server uses your Lovable user permissions — it can only access workspaces you already have access to."}];function sie({nonce:e}){return(0,a.jsxs)("div",{children:[(0,a.jsx)(Lp,{schema:m0(Qd),nonce:e}),(0,a.jsx)(WU,{}),(0,a.jsxs)(kb,{children:[(0,a.jsxs)(Zs,{hasPadding:!0,className:"bg-muted",children:[(0,a.jsxs)(rc,{className:"mb-12 max-w-3xl",animate:!0,children:[(0,a.jsx)(In,{tag:"h2",children:"Everything an agent needs to ship a real app"}),(0,a.jsx)(Nr,{size:"medium",children:"The Lovable MCP server exposes the same primitives Lovable runs on: projects, chat, files, connectors, databases, and deploys, as tools any agent can call."})]}),(0,a.jsx)(Zu,{className:"grid grid-cols-1 gap-2 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3",children:KU.map(t=>(0,a.jsx)(OU,{title:t.title,description:t.description,icon:t.icon,iconClassName:t.iconClassName},t.title))})]}),(0,a.jsx)(Zs,{id:"setup",hasPadding:!0,children:(0,a.jsxs)("div",{className:"mx-auto max-w-3xl",children:[(0,a.jsxs)(rc,{className:"mb-8",animate:!0,children:[(0,a.jsx)(In,{tag:"h2",children:"Connect your client"}),(0,a.jsx)(Nr,{size:"medium",children:"Pick your client and follow the steps. Authentication uses OAuth, so there are no API keys to manage."})]}),(0,a.jsx)(XU,{}),(0,a.jsxs)("div",{className:"mt-8 flex flex-col items-start gap-3 sm:flex-row",children:[(0,a.jsx)(hu,{href:"https://docs.lovable.dev/integrations/lovable-mcp-server",openInNewTab:!0,children:"Read the full docs"}),(0,a.jsx)(wu,{href:"/pricing",children:"View pricing"})]})]})})]}),(0,a.jsx)(Zs,{className:"bg-muted",children:(0,a.jsx)(jv,{faqs:Qd,title:"Frequently asked questions"})})]})}var JU=()=>h(()=>import("./mcp-APYG7FvD.js"),__vite__mapDeps([882,9,1,3,4,5])),QU=_("/_marketing/mcp/")({head:()=>Y({title:HU,description:z